WEBVTT

1
00:00:53.941 --> 00:00:57.361
- Remember when they used to let commercial airlines land in this town?
- Yeah.

2
00:00:57.444 --> 00:00:59.697
Well, I don't understand where we're going...

3
00:00:59.780 --> 00:01:01.950
...or why the hell we're bothering anyhow.

4
00:01:02.117 --> 00:01:05.161
- You're doing a good deed.
- Wanna give us a better reason?

5
00:01:05.278 --> 00:01:09.416
Yeah. A maniac hijacked a municipal bus with 30
passengers on it. That's a very good reason.

6
00:01:09.874 --> 00:01:13.379
And I got a real bad hunch where those passengers are
and who that maniac is.

7
00:01:13.462 --> 00:01:14.880
You wanna share it with us?

8
00:01:15.506 --> 00:01:16.549
Phoenix.

9
00:01:17.133 --> 00:01:18.384
Simon Phoenix.

10
00:01:55.632 --> 00:01:57.676
Send a maniac to catch one.

11
00:01:59.712 --> 00:02:02.913
Phoenix!

12
00:03:13.675 --> 00:03:15.427
Don't move, Phoenix.

13
00:03:19.014 --> 00:03:20.558
You're under arrest.

14
00:03:21.225 --> 00:03:22.768
Arrest? Shit.

15
00:03:23.561 --> 00:03:25.271
And you're trespassing.

16
00:03:26.605 --> 00:03:28.024
Where are the passengers?

17
00:03:28.108 --> 00:03:30.152
Oh, yes, passengers.

18
00:03:30.318 --> 00:03:31.862
Well, they're....

19
00:03:32.946 --> 00:03:34.197
Fuck you.

20
00:03:34.281 --> 00:03:36.158
The passengers are gone.

21
00:03:36.616 --> 00:03:40.120
See, I told the city, I said
"Look, nobody comes down here."

22
00:03:40.747 --> 00:03:42.457
Postmen figured it out...

23
00:03:42.623 --> 00:03:44.208
...policemen figured it out.

24
00:03:44.292 --> 00:03:47.587
But the goddamn bus drivers
just wouldn't listen.

25
00:03:48.212 --> 00:03:50.006
Last time, Phoenix.

26
00:03:50.381 --> 00:03:52.383
Where are the hostages?

27
00:03:52.508 --> 00:03:55.763
To hell with the hostages!
This is between you and me!

28
00:04:00.642 --> 00:04:01.727
What you got, soldier boy?

29
00:04:01.810 --> 00:04:02.895
Do something.

30
00:04:02.978 --> 00:04:04.271
Go ahead.

31
00:04:05.231 --> 00:04:07.400
You're up to your ass in gasoline.

32
00:04:10.779 --> 00:04:12.655
I'll set your ass on fire.

33
00:04:25.795 --> 00:04:27.380
Is it cold in here...

34
00:04:28.130 --> 00:04:29.673
...or is it just me?

35
00:05:01.917 --> 00:05:03.377
Where are they, Phoenix?

36
00:05:03.460 --> 00:05:05.212
Now, where did I put them?

37
00:05:05.504 --> 00:05:08.758
I swear, I'd lose my head
if it wasn't attached.

38
00:05:10.093 --> 00:05:12.095
I'll keep that in mind.

39
00:05:53.639 --> 00:05:56.810
Damn it, John. I'm tired
of this "Demolition-Man" shit!

40
00:05:57.269 --> 00:05:59.521
You were not supposed
to come down here!

41
00:05:59.605 --> 00:06:03.192
You were not supposed to attempt
the arrest of Phoenix single-handed...

42
00:06:03.242 --> 00:06:04.943
...and you were not supposed to blow anything up!

43
00:06:05.027 --> 00:06:08.197
It's not me, this time, Healy. He dumped the gas
and rigged the place to blow!

44
00:06:08.280 --> 00:06:09.949
Yeah right, you had nothing to do with it.

45
00:06:10.033 --> 00:06:12.660
I know you've been trying
to nail this psycho for 2 years.

46
00:06:12.744 --> 00:06:14.704
But try remembering a little thing called...

47
00:06:14.871 --> 00:06:16.623
...official police procedure.

48
00:06:16.706 --> 00:06:18.666
- Where are the hostages?
- They're not here.

49
00:06:18.750 --> 00:06:19.459
What do you mean they are not here?

50
00:06:19.542 --> 00:06:21.462
He must've stashed them someplace else!

51
00:06:21.545 --> 00:06:23.422
How do you know they weren't in there? Are you sure?

52
00:06:23.506 --> 00:06:27.051
Because I did a thermo check and there
was only eight of them, all part of his gang.

53
00:06:27.134 --> 00:06:28.302
Wrong again!

54
00:06:28.469 --> 00:06:30.221
You got something to say, scumbag?

55
00:06:31.138 --> 00:06:32.681
Get him out of here!

56
00:06:33.475 --> 00:06:34.518
Motherfucker!

57
00:06:34.601 --> 00:06:36.853
You and I gonna have a nice long chat.

58
00:06:37.729 --> 00:06:38.730
Captain!

59
00:06:39.731 --> 00:06:42.192
Over here! There's bodies everywhere!

60
00:06:42.317 --> 00:06:43.860
There must be 20 or 30.

61
00:06:43.944 --> 00:06:45.446
They're everywhere.

62
00:06:46.823 --> 00:06:48.241
See that, Captain? I told him!

63
00:06:48.324 --> 00:06:50.159
He said he didn't care!

64
00:06:50.451 --> 00:06:54.205
How could you sacrifice
all those innocent people for me!

65
00:06:54.956 --> 00:06:56.749
What kind of man are you?

66
00:06:56.833 --> 00:07:00.170
We're gonna spend a lot of quality time together.
See you, sweetie!

67
00:07:00.254 --> 00:07:01.797
Honey! Sugar!

68
00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:05.175
If you got a lawyer, you better call him.

69
00:08:01.528 --> 00:08:05.115
John Spartan, you've done great deeds
for the city of Los Angeles.

70
00:08:05.574 --> 00:08:08.827
So, it is with some regret that, I,
William Smithers...

71
00:08:08.952 --> 00:08:12.499
...acting as Assistant Warden,
hereby carry out this sentence.

72
00:08:12.749 --> 00:08:14.042
Skip it.

73
00:08:15.085 --> 00:08:17.253
Sargeant Spartan, you've been sentenced to 70 years...

74
00:08:17.337 --> 00:08:21.591
...sub-zero re-habilitation
in the California Cryo-Penitentiary...

75
00:08:21.883 --> 00:08:25.262
...for the involuntary manslaughter
of 30 innocent civilians.

76
00:08:25.638 --> 00:08:26.806
Skip it.

77
00:08:26.931 --> 00:08:30.351
You'll be placed in cryo-stasis
for the duration of your sentence...

78
00:08:30.434 --> 00:08:33.979
...during which your behavior will be altered
through synaptic suggestion.

79
00:08:34.063 --> 00:08:37.526
You'll be eligible for parole
no earlier than the year 2046.

80
00:08:46.451 --> 00:08:47.577
I'm sorry, Sargeant.

81
00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:51.735
"All personnel..."

82
00:11:51.818 --> 00:11:55.448
"...the next scheduled parole hearing
for prisoner Gilmour..."

83
00:11:55.573 --> 00:11:57.617
"...will take place at 07:15"

84
00:11:58.910 --> 00:12:02.747
"Warden William Smithers
report to Level A, conference room"

85
00:12:09.088 --> 00:12:10.506
Mellow greetings, Warden William Smithers.

86
00:12:11.173 --> 00:12:13.717
Be well, Lieutenant Lenina Huxley.

87
00:12:14.593 --> 00:12:16.428
As it is a beautiful...

88
00:12:16.595 --> 00:12:20.308
...Monday morning and as my duty log
irrationally requires it...

89
00:12:20.475 --> 00:12:23.144
...I'm hereby querying you
on the prison population update.

90
00:12:23.228 --> 00:12:24.979
Does the tedium continue?

91
00:12:25.105 --> 00:12:27.816
Your earnest questioning is as amusing as it is irrelevant.

92
00:12:27.941 --> 00:12:30.610
The prisoners are ice cubes.
They never move.

93
00:12:31.320 --> 00:12:34.407
I find this lack of stimulus
to be truly disappointing.

94
00:12:34.490 --> 00:12:36.242
- Don't you think?
- I try not to.

95
00:12:36.325 --> 00:12:38.661
However, you're young, think all you want.

96
00:12:38.828 --> 00:12:41.872
Things don't happen anymore,
we've taken care of all that.

97
00:12:41.956 --> 00:12:44.793
I'll fiber-op you back
after the parole hearings.

98
00:12:44.876 --> 00:12:46.461
Have a peachy day, Lieutenant.

99
00:12:46.628 --> 00:12:47.671
Be well.

100
00:12:47.838 --> 00:12:48.713
Be well.

101
00:12:48.797 --> 00:12:50.215
"Vector 137"

102
00:12:50.298 --> 00:12:52.801
"Upcoming, Santa Monica Boulevard"

103
00:12:58.015 --> 00:12:59.725
"Retina coding accepted"

104
00:12:59.892 --> 00:13:01.978
"Warden William Smithers, be well"

105
00:13:02.395 --> 00:13:03.479
Go on.

106
00:13:11.572 --> 00:13:12.656
Self-drive on.

107
00:13:12.740 --> 00:13:14.533
"Self-drive engaged"

108
00:13:14.908 --> 00:13:16.285
Huxley, Lenina, coding on.

109
00:13:16.577 --> 00:13:20.331
"No police presence is requested
in the city at this time"

110
00:13:20.498 --> 00:13:21.666
"Report to the station"

111
00:13:21.750 --> 00:13:23.668
Oh boy, how exciting.

112
00:13:59.415 --> 00:14:00.416
That's it.

113
00:14:00.500 --> 00:14:02.335
Food, glorious food.

114
00:14:03.044 --> 00:14:04.462
There'll be another one in about 12 hours.

115
00:14:04.545 --> 00:14:06.923
These assholes are nothing if not predictable.

116
00:14:07.298 --> 00:14:08.841
God, I love to hate this place!

117
00:14:08.925 --> 00:14:10.594
There's not enough of us, Friendly.

118
00:14:10.677 --> 00:14:12.679
That doesn't really matter anymore, does it Crow?

119
00:14:12.763 --> 00:14:14.139
People are hungry.

120
00:14:14.223 --> 00:14:16.141
We've got nothing left to lose.

121
00:14:29.989 --> 00:14:31.324
Greetings, Merwin.

122
00:14:31.491 --> 00:14:33.034
Lovely Lenina.

123
00:14:34.954 --> 00:14:38.457
Greetings and salutations. Welcome
to the emergency line of the SAPD.

124
00:14:39.333 --> 00:14:42.336
If you prefer an automated response,
press 1 now.

125
00:14:42.503 --> 00:14:43.796
Be well.

126
00:14:47.175 --> 00:14:49.177
Mellow greetings, Lenina Huxley.

127
00:14:49.261 --> 00:14:51.263
Let me guess, all is serene?

128
00:14:51.471 --> 00:14:54.266
On the contrary, it's been a horrific a.m.

129
00:14:54.683 --> 00:14:56.852
There was a defacement of public buildings.

130
00:14:57.018 --> 00:14:58.896
Walls smudged with...

131
00:14:59.355 --> 00:15:01.023
...scandalous graffiti.

132
00:15:01.107 --> 00:15:02.191
Really?

133
00:15:02.358 --> 00:15:05.319
Brutal. Why wasn't there
an "all-cars notify"?

134
00:15:05.528 --> 00:15:09.031
Because there was no need
to create widespread panic.

135
00:15:10.116 --> 00:15:11.869
Lieutenant Huxley...

136
00:15:12.035 --> 00:15:15.038
...I monitored your disheartening
and distressing comments...

137
00:15:15.122 --> 00:15:17.040
...to the warden this morning.

138
00:15:17.124 --> 00:15:20.127
Do you really long for chaos
and disharmony?

139
00:15:21.003 --> 00:15:24.758
Your fascination with the vulgar 20th century
seems to be affecting your better judgment.

140
00:15:25.717 --> 00:15:29.637
You realize you're setting a bad example
for other officers and sworn personnel.

141
00:15:29.721 --> 00:15:32.390
Thank you for the attitude re-adjustment, Chief Earle.

142
00:15:32.557 --> 00:15:34.267
Info assimilated.

143
00:15:42.067 --> 00:15:43.736
Sanctimonious asshole.

144
00:15:43.903 --> 00:15:46.572
"Lenina Huxley, you are fined one half credit..."

145
00:15:46.655 --> 00:15:49.743
"...for a 'sotto voce' violation
of the verbal-morality statute"

146
00:15:49.826 --> 00:15:51.203
Thank you.

147
00:15:58.251 --> 00:15:59.586
That was tense.

148
00:15:59.920 --> 00:16:01.506
- That was tense?
- Yes.

149
00:16:02.491 --> 00:16:07.929
Tell me something, Garcia? Don't you get bored
code tracing perps who break curfew and tell dirty jokes?

150
00:16:07.987 --> 00:16:10.473
Actually, no. I find my job deeply fulfilling.

151
00:16:11.265 --> 00:16:14.937
I just can not get over the reality
of this office, Lenina Huxley.

152
00:16:15.437 --> 00:16:17.898
You're still addicted to the 20th century.

153
00:16:17.981 --> 00:16:21.276
High from its harshness.
Buzzed by its brutality.

154
00:16:21.693 --> 00:16:23.153
Holy smokes!

155
00:16:23.779 --> 00:16:28.034
Is there anything in this office which
doesn't violate Contraband Ordinance 22?

156
00:16:28.118 --> 00:16:29.452
Only you, Alfredo Garcia.

157
00:16:31.079 --> 00:16:33.581
Don't you ever want something to happen?

158
00:16:34.791 --> 00:16:36.084
Goodness, no.

159
00:16:36.876 --> 00:16:38.629
I knew you were gonna say that.

160
00:16:41.465 --> 00:16:43.634
What I wouldn't give for some action.

161
00:16:54.438 --> 00:16:56.189
Mr. Simon Phoenix.

162
00:16:57.399 --> 00:17:00.110
One of our first
and most illustrious members.

163
00:17:01.486 --> 00:17:02.655
Allow me to...

164
00:17:02.780 --> 00:17:05.658
...welcome you to your parole hearing.

165
00:17:06.033 --> 00:17:07.952
Let's get this over quickly.

166
00:17:10.955 --> 00:17:14.793
Twenty-nine years ago,
the parole system, as you know it...

167
00:17:16.795 --> 00:17:18.881
...was rendered obsolete.

168
00:17:20.799 --> 00:17:22.926
Federal Statute 537-29....

169
00:17:27.307 --> 00:17:28.349
Stop it!

170
00:17:31.936 --> 00:17:34.814
Do you have anything fresh to say
on your behalf?

171
00:17:38.485 --> 00:17:39.820
I thought not.

172
00:17:42.573 --> 00:17:43.491
Yeah.

173
00:17:43.699 --> 00:17:44.867
I do.

174
00:17:45.826 --> 00:17:46.994
Teddy bear.

175
00:18:04.764 --> 00:18:06.682
How'd you know the password to the cuffs?

176
00:18:06.933 --> 00:18:08.434
I wish I knew.

177
00:18:08.518 --> 00:18:10.186
Simon says: Die.

178
00:18:28.706 --> 00:18:29.874
Warden...

179
00:18:30.542 --> 00:18:32.585
...let's get this over quickly.

180
00:18:39.759 --> 00:18:43.013
"Retina coding accepted,
Warden William Smithers"

181
00:18:44.265 --> 00:18:45.266
"Be well"

182
00:18:45.808 --> 00:18:47.268
Yeah, you too.

183
00:18:50.563 --> 00:18:51.939
"187. 187."

184
00:18:53.191 --> 00:18:55.277
"Northwest quadrant. 187."

185
00:19:02.659 --> 00:19:03.910
Oh, my!

186
00:19:05.746 --> 00:19:07.498
I don't believe it!

187
00:19:07.832 --> 00:19:09.917
"Northwest quadrant. 187."

188
00:19:11.586 --> 00:19:13.087
What's a 187?

189
00:19:13.254 --> 00:19:14.505
I don't know.

190
00:19:14.589 --> 00:19:15.548
"Cryo-prison"

191
00:19:15.631 --> 00:19:16.924
"Level 6"

192
00:19:17.759 --> 00:19:19.511
"Identify Code 187."

193
00:19:22.765 --> 00:19:23.891
"M-D-K"

194
00:19:25.184 --> 00:19:26.769
"MurderDeathKill"

195
00:19:29.646 --> 00:19:30.815
MurderDeathKill!

196
00:19:30.899 --> 00:19:33.777
"Last recorded offense, September 25, 2010"

197
00:19:34.444 --> 00:19:36.780
"Initiate search, confirming location"

198
00:19:36.863 --> 00:19:38.698
"Cryo-prison, Level 6"

199
00:19:40.784 --> 00:19:43.788
"Two code 187's:
Officer John D'Argent, guard"

200
00:19:43.954 --> 00:19:45.623
"Officer Alfred Pamela, guard"

201
00:19:45.706 --> 00:19:46.624
"Tracking"

202
00:19:46.707 --> 00:19:50.628
"Live transmission diagnostic check,
Warden William Smithers"

203
00:19:50.795 --> 00:19:53.964
"Injuries: Severe eye trauma,
ruptured spleen..."

204
00:19:54.089 --> 00:19:55.383
"...punctured lung..."

205
00:19:55.467 --> 00:19:57.803
"...broken rib, internal bleeding"

206
00:19:57.969 --> 00:19:59.513
"Condition critical"

207
00:19:59.596 --> 00:20:01.181
"Vital signs failing"

208
00:20:01.264 --> 00:20:02.724
"Imminent death"

209
00:20:06.311 --> 00:20:07.730
"Subject deceased"

210
00:20:08.022 --> 00:20:10.399
"187, Warden William Smithers..."

211
00:20:10.900 --> 00:20:13.236
"...born February 14th, 1967..."

212
00:20:14.320 --> 00:20:16.405
"...died August 4th, 2032"

213
00:20:17.406 --> 00:20:20.035
- What's the matter with all of you?
- The cryo-prison, sir.

214
00:20:20.119 --> 00:20:21.995
Three non-sanctioned life terminations.

215
00:20:22.079 --> 00:20:24.414
"Do you wish to assign a coroner?"

216
00:20:25.374 --> 00:20:26.834
MurderDeathKills!

217
00:20:27.167 --> 00:20:28.502
Three MDKs!

218
00:20:32.423 --> 00:20:34.926
Access for me the cryo-pen's morning hearing schedule...

219
00:20:35.009 --> 00:20:37.262
...and display for me the list of people interviewed
for parole.

220
00:20:37.345 --> 00:20:41.099
"Accessing cryo-prison processing.
Restricted information"

221
00:20:41.182 --> 00:20:43.935
"Cocteau Cryo-prison,
morning hearing schedule"

222
00:20:44.061 --> 00:20:46.021
"August 4th, active file"

223
00:20:46.105 --> 00:20:47.690
"7:00 a.m.: Hyde, Quentin"

224
00:20:47.773 --> 00:20:49.692
"8:15: Peterson, Scott"

225
00:20:49.859 --> 00:20:51.694
"7:30: Phoenix, Simon"
- It's Phoenix!

226
00:20:51.777 --> 00:20:53.028
"7:45...."
- Who?

227
00:20:53.112 --> 00:20:54.655
Simon Phoenix.

228
00:20:56.483 --> 00:20:57.783
"Phoenix, Simon"

229
00:20:57.784 --> 00:20:59.161
"Accessing..."
- I knew him.

230
00:20:59.244 --> 00:21:02.205
He's evil in a way you've never read about.

231
00:21:02.497 --> 00:21:05.709
He's a criminal the likes
of which you've never seen.

232
00:21:05.876 --> 00:21:07.627
Hold that thought, Zachary Lamb.

233
00:21:10.006 --> 00:21:11.299
Simon Phoenix's code, now.

234
00:21:11.382 --> 00:21:13.426
"Access code for Phoenix, Simon"

235
00:21:14.135 --> 00:21:17.263
"No code found"
- L-7, you're not coming down with another virus, are you?

236
00:21:17.555 --> 00:21:20.057
"Of course not"
- You don't get it, Lenina Huxley.

237
00:21:20.976 --> 00:21:22.478
Phoenix isn't coded.

238
00:21:22.561 --> 00:21:24.646
He was chilled back in the 20th...

239
00:21:24.813 --> 00:21:27.024
...before they started lo-jacking everybody.

240
00:21:27.107 --> 00:21:30.194
Declared his own kingdom
in South Central LA.

241
00:21:30.402 --> 00:21:31.737
In a bad time...

242
00:21:32.237 --> 00:21:34.824
- ...he was the worst.
- Emergency, code 187.

243
00:21:35.408 --> 00:21:37.243
"Emergency, Code 187."

244
00:21:39.245 --> 00:21:40.872
"Locating stopped code"

245
00:21:41.080 --> 00:21:43.500
"MurderDeathKill. MurderDeathKill"

246
00:21:44.375 --> 00:21:45.376
"Location..."

247
00:21:45.460 --> 00:21:49.048
"...Cryo-prison, parking area.
Cryo-prison, Level 6...."

248
00:21:49.749 --> 00:21:50.249
No.

249
00:21:50.591 --> 00:21:52.593
"Main cryo-prison parking zone"

250
00:21:52.718 --> 00:21:54.345
"Enhancing image"

251
00:21:54.678 --> 00:21:56.472
"Tracking Dr. Mostow"
- Oh, my.

252
00:21:56.806 --> 00:21:58.350
"187, deceased"

253
00:22:00.227 --> 00:22:02.437
"Do you wish to assign a coroner?"

254
00:22:03.706 --> 00:22:06.108
Tell me, L-7, is the doctor's conveyance still in the parking zone?

255
00:22:06.191 --> 00:22:08.568
"The answer is no. Car missing"

256
00:22:10.404 --> 00:22:14.283
"Doctor's conveyance is not
in parking zone. It is in motion"

257
